Appendix 2 . Comparison of morphological characters, and univariate results for discriminant function analyses based on 24 and 23 variables for males and females respectively. Data are mean ± standard deviation, with the range of measures indicated in parentheses.All morphometric measures are in mm and sample sizes are listed in the column headings. ANOVA results are presented in the statistics column. Statistically significant values after false discovery rate correction are in bold, *P <0.05, **P <0.01, ***P <0.001.
